                            in the earlier version of the contraption. Each of these solar powered lamps are made using sturdy <b>PVC pipes, reused water bottles, and solar panels </b>all of which can be fitted and used for
                            various applications - such as street lights. As an estimate, each street light costs around <b>Rs. 2500 - 3000.</b> The villagers are even educated about the products to the extent that these installations become self sustaining.

                            <br><br>
                            <div style="text-align:center;">
                                <img alt="flutur" src="http://res.cloudinary.com/epicfoundation/image/upload/v1524747101/old-plastic-bottles-have-now-been-used-to-light-up-more-than-850000-homes-around-the-world_bjhrfg.jpg" style="width:90%">
